1
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:07,120
Once that shipment arrives,

2
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,960
his life will fall into the gutter.

3
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,080
You must return to Phuket
to claim your inheritance.

4
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:15,120
This is an enormous fortune.

5
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:17,480
Why would he leave all this to me?

6
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,200
Wild Bull!

7
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,040
I'm about to become a rich man.

8
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,800
I'm inheriting a fortune from my uncle.

9
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,240
He's a wealthy man in Phuket.

10
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:34,360
<i>I need you to go to Phuket</i>
<i>and claim the inheritance in my place.</i>

11
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,280
How many more hours until we reach Phuket?

12
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,040
I'm dead. I'm absolutely dead.

13
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,280
Is this Som Song Saeng residence?

14
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,080
I'm Thatri.

15
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,760
DEAR MS. SUANG

16
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:03,920
This is indeed the letter
I sent to Mr. Thatri.

17
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,720
Congratulations on making it on time.

18
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,280
I'm Fuangfah.

19
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,760
This is Paetai.

20
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:17,040
We're both nieces of Aunt Saeng,
Uncle Som's wife.

21
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:25,280
Hold on. You just show up with a letter?

22
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,840
Anyone could claim to be him.

23
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:29,080
How do we know you're the real one?

24
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:33,720
Do you have any ID card
to verify your identity?

25
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:35,800
It would put her at ease.

26
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,440
You know that ID cards

27
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,840
are only issued in the Bangkok
and Thonburi provinces.

28
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:44,800
I'm from Nakhon Sawan. I don't have it.

29
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,560
You could be an impostor
who stole the letter.

30
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,040
I suggest

31
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,400
we postpone the reading of the will.

32
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,280
Not until we prove that he's the real one.

33
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,240
Sister,

34
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:03,080
aren't we being a bit of a sore loser?

35
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,080
Ugh!

36
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,920
Keep your mouth shut.

37
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:22,560
This here

38
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:24,920
is my certificate of employment

39
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,680
from the State Railway Department.

40
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,080
CERTIFICATE OF EMPLOYMENT

41
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,400
Can you see?

42
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,160
It says Thatri right here.

43
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,800
MR. THATRI VORAPAT

44
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,720
The paperwork is in order.

45
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,120
I trust this clears up any doubts?

46
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,280
You must be exhausted from your journey.
Please, go and rest.

47
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,280
I'll have someone attend to you.

48
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:52,080
- Thank you.
- Right this way.

49
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:05,400
Another claimant…

50
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:08,080
As if Rajit taking a slice wasn't enough.

51
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:10,040
Why didn't he just fall overboard and die?

52
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,480
Well?

53
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,240
Go do your job.

54
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,680
Yes, madam.

55
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,560
That fortune belongs to me.

56
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:27,360
I won't let anyone steal it from me.

57
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,240
Thank you so much.

58
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,040
I'm Thatri.

59
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,040
I know. Miss Fuang already told me.

60
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,760
Anyway, I'm Nid,

61
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:46,000
and this is my grandmother, Jiam.

62
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,240
If you need anything,

63
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,480
just let us know.

64
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,840
Shut your mouth, Nid.

65
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:56,240
He's just here for the inheritance.

66
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,960
Once he gets the money, he'll be gone.

67
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,640
He won't be staying here long.

68
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,560
What kind of day is this?

69
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:15,680
Nothing but trouble,

70
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,560
and everyone I meet is off their rocker.

71
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,360
Thief!

72
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,600
Help! A thief!

73
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,440
Everyone, wake up!

74
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,400
Don't!

75
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,560
Trying to run?

76
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,320
Stop!

77
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:20,160
Stop right there.

78
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,880
Get off me!

79
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,280
- Let me go!
- A woman?

80
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:30,080
That doesn't excuse you for being a thief.

81
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,360
We're going to the police.

82
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:33,320
No!

83
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,800
Let go!

84
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,040
Huh?

85
00:07:56,120 --> 00:08:00,000
That arrogant guy you were badmouthing
is your uncle?

86
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:03,400
Yes. Talk about a small world.

87
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,680
And now we're stuck
living under the same roof.

88
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,160
What karma did I commit

89
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,880
to end up with a psycho for an uncle?

90
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:18,840
Uncle Ree, how long
have you been standing there?

91
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,400
Ever since I became

92
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,280
the psycho to you and your friends.

93
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:37,039
I'm here to apologize for last night.
I didn't mean to hurt you.

94
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,159
My apologies.

95
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,919
He makes a mistake and then apologizes…

96
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,400
So incredibly handsome!

97
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:50,960
It's okay.

98
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,640
I'm not hurt that bad.

99
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:55,080
Besides, it wasn't your fault, Uncle Ree.

100
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,120
I arrived near dawn

101
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,400
and didn't want to wake anyone.

102
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,480
I figured I'd climb up to my room

103
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:03,760
just like I did when I was little.

104
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,400
Fair enough.

105
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,600
But tell me.

106
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,840
Why do you keep calling me Uncle Ree?

107
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:17,000
Well, your name is Thatri.

108
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,520
When I got the letter from Vijarn,

109
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,360
the font confused me,

110
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:24,040
so I misread it as That-Ree.

111
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,280
I, MR. SOM ADISUAN, HEREBY DELACRE
THAT I AM OF SOUND MIND AND MEMORY

112
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,120
MR. THATRI VORAPAT

113
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,880
That's why I called you Uncle Ree.

114
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,520
Who on earth is named That-Ree?

115
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,240
Don't you have any common sense?

116
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:49,120
Why couldn't there be someone
named That-Ree?

117
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,960
Why are you lecturing me?

118
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,080
I'm not lecturing you,

119
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,840
I'm trying to teach you some common sense.

120
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,480
Stop making excuses.

121
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,640
Alright.

122
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,440
Thank you for your wisdom,

123
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,920
Uncle Ree.

124
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:12,680
Even his angry face is adorable.

125
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,640
I just want to go and comfort him.

126
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:15,720
See?

127
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,920
Exactly what I told you.

128
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,200
Yeah,

129
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,320
saw it with my own eyes.

130
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,240
- So handsome.
- So handsome.

131
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,640
He's nothing like you described.

132
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,720
You're just being biased.

133
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:29,240
True. He's an adult,

134
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:32,960
so what's the big deal
if he wants to lecture or guide you?

135
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,040
Totally. You even accused him

136
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,640
of being narcissistic

137
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:39,360
or a psycho. You're so mean.

138
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:43,800
So you're siding with a guy
over your own friend?

139
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:55,880
That girl… If she were my kin,
I'd give her a real spanking.

140
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,880
No one is as annoying as her.

141
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,360
You're quite jumpy, aren't you?

142
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,240
Maybe you should try it yourself.

143
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:09,520
The lawyer sent me to get you.
All the relatives are here.

144
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,560
The will reading is about to begin?

145
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:13,800
Not yet.

146
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:16,640
The will can only be opened
the day after tomorrow.

147
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,840
Why can't we open it now?

148
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:22,520
Everyone's already here.
What are we waiting for?

149
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,880
Even those who've never lifted a finger

150
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,720
are here to claim their share.

151
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,480
I am following
the instructions stated in the will.

152
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:37,240
It explicitly states

153
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,280
that it must be opened
the day after tomorrow.

154
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:42,000
Why the unnecessary hassle?

155
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,640
It's actually Grandfather Som's birthday.

156
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,240
I suspect

157
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:49,040
he probably wanted the will
to be read on that day.

158
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,880
Don't you remember his birthday, Uncle?

159
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:57,600
We've waited this long,
two more days shouldn't be a problem.

160
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:59,480
Sure, you perfect little angel.

161
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:03,360
I suppose we'll return in two days.

162
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,880
I just hope Uncle Som

163
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,680
was fair enough

164
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:09,240
to split the estate equally
among all of us.

165
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:12,000
I assume he didn't just favor
his own side of the family.

166
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,080
Equal shares?

167
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,520
You get out what you put in.

168
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,640
Otherwise, all the lazy freeloaders
would be getting a free ride.

169
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,160
- Whoa.
- Sister.

170
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,080
- What?
- Who are you talking about?

171
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,560
I'm talking about you.

172
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:29,760
All you ever did was kiss up to Uncle Som.

173
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:31,720
I've never seen you do
a day's work in your life.

174
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,560
The moment the will is read,
you show your face here.

175
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:36,360
Fuang and I

176
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,520
have been breaking our backs
working for this.

177
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:41,000
Equal shares? Over my dead body.

178
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,960
Fine!

179
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:44,440
Maybe I'll just do that right now!

180
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:46,480
Come on!

181
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,840
- Bring it on!
- Please, stop!

182
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,080
Let's keep our cool. I'm begging you.

183
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:53,200
Uncle Som just passed away.
Let's not do this right now.

184
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,040
Watch your mouth.

185
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:58,360
- Don't point at me!
- Sister, stop.

186
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,200
Alright, let's go.

187
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,520
They're so greedy.

188
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:19,320
Lawyer, I have a question.

189
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,880
Go ahead, please.

190
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,440
In Uncle Som's letter,

191
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:25,200
it said Rajit and I
were splitting the estate equally.

192
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,760
How come none of the relatives
know about this?

193
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,480
It was Mr. Som's wish.

194
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:38,360
He feared the inheritance
would put you both in danger.

195
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,880
He ordered me to keep it a secret

196
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,520
until everything is settled.

197
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,560
Are you scared, Uncle Ree?

198
00:13:58,760 --> 00:13:59,840
Yes, I am.

199
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:05,000
But when I realize
I'll be living with you,

200
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,080
suddenly, nothing else seems that scary.

201
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:29,040
SOM ADISUAN

202
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,320
Grandpa, I've come to pay my respects.

203
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:34,080
I'm so sorry

204
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,360
I wasn't here to see you one last time.

205
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:42,120
I'll never forget
what you did for me, Grandpa.

206
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:46,200
Unlike some people,

207
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,280
they only care about your fortune.

208
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:53,480
They can't even be bothered
to pay their respects here,

209
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:56,240
nor do they care to ask where I am.

210
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:00,120
Sounds like she's tattling to Grandpa now.

211
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,600
Tell me about it.

212
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,840
Primprao, Nareewan!

213
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,240
- Oops.
- Oops.

214
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,920
Whoever forgets you is their own business.

215
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,880
I promise

216
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:18,680
I'll guard your fortune with my life.

217
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:23,120
I won't let anyone belittle me

218
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,760
or say I can't manage it.

219
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:40,080
Still fuming over Uncle Ree?

220
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:43,280
He's actually quite polite, and he's…

221
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,080
fun to talk to.

222
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,360
A heartless guy like that,

223
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,360
I don't know how you two

224
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:53,600
can be so obsessed with him.

225
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,200
But he's so handsome.

226
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:01,880
He sure is, but his personality is trash.

227
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:07,080
He didn't even ask
where Grandpa's remains were kept.

228
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:09,080
All he cares about is the fortune.

229
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:18,880
What is it?

230
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,440
Nothing.

231
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:27,080
Anyway, I'll see you at the house.

232
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:28,880
I'm heading off.

233
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:32,360
- Oh?
- Oh?

234
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,720
- Uncle Ree.
- Why are you following me?

235
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:10,240
Following you? Who's following?

236
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:12,280
I'm just taking a walk,

237
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:13,720
I'm not following you at all.

238
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,160
What a blatant lie.

239
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,400
I've known you were
tailing me the whole time,

240
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,920
so I led you here on purpose.

241
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:25,920
Now, tell me, why are you stalking me?

242
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,880
I was just following you to see

243
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:31,240
what you were up to.

244
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:40,760
Snatcher!

245
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:42,320
Help!

246
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,440
Help me! He snatched my purse!

247
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,680
Get out of the way!

248
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,600
Two baht?

249
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,480
A bowl of noodles only costs five satang.

250
00:18:57,560 --> 00:18:59,840
Two baht isn't exactly
a small amount, Uncle Ree.

251
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,160
But it wasn't worth
the risk of chasing a thief.

252
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,240
Dying over two baht,

253
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:06,520
that would be pathetic.

254
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:07,760
Why didn't you tell me

255
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:09,440
you only had a tiny amount on you?

256
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:12,680
Even if it's a little,
it's still money, isn't it?

257
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:14,080
When you have nothing,

258
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,720
even that counts.

259
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:19,440
You shouldn't look down
on the value of money like that.

260
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,280
But anyway…

261
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,920
I apologize

262
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,000
I didn't tell you I only had two baht.

263
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:39,600
And… thank you

264
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:43,240
for chasing the thief
and getting my money back.

265
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:48,240
Just be more careful next time.

266
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:50,520
During wartime,
there are a lot of people struggling,

267
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:53,280
and thieves are everywhere.

268
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:57,680
Okay, Uncle Ree.

269
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,160
Now, can you answer me?

270
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,320
Why were you following me?

271
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:07,400
It's you who needs to answer me.

272
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:09,080
Where exactly are you heading?

273
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:12,000
As far as I know,

274
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:14,640
this is your first time in Phuket.

275
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:17,800
You shouldn't have any business anywhere.

276
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,320
Right?

277
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,600
Well, Uncle Ree?

278
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,640
DOCTOR SOMSAK

279
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,280
This little guy is a real fighter.

280
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:34,960
He survived the night,
so I think he's out of the woods.

281
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,880
Thank you so much, Doctor.
How much do I owe you?

282
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:46,360
I won't charge for the treatment.
Just pay for the medicine.

283
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:50,600
Something wrong?

284
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,400
Just a moment, please.

285
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,120
I'll wait outside.

286
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,720
You should've told me

287
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,520
you were taking the dog to the vet.

288
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:07,360
I wouldn't have had to tag along.

289
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,240
It's a good thing you did.

290
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:12,280
If you hadn't, I'd be in real trouble.

291
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:14,800
Why?

292
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,320
You have two baht on you, right?

293
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:24,160
Let me borrow it.
I don't have enough to pay.

294
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,680
Let me borrow it. Consider it

295
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:33,560
a tip for risking my life
to get your bag back.

296
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:40,600
Fine.

297
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,440
Here's the two baht.

298
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,080
Thank you.

299
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,840
He even took the two baht.

300
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,840
What kind of elder does that?

301
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:24,800
But he used the money to help a dog.
I think that's sweet.

302
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,800
You followed him there.

303
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,000
Why are you complaining?

304
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,120
Today, I got robbed,

305
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:33,040
I lost my money. What kind of day is this?

306
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,200
Uncle Ree?

307
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,400
What on earth are you doing?

308
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:50,040
I couldn't sleep last night.
Must be the new environment.

309
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:52,440
I figured if I exercised and got tired,
I'd sleep like a log.

310
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:55,040
Then why not do it in your room?

311
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,720
Why are you doing this right out here?

312
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,400
It's airy out here.

313
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:07,240
Here's a towel.

314
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,080
Let me dry you off.

315
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:17,240
I was the one who grabbed the towel,

316
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:19,200
so I should be the one to do it.

317
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,240
It doesn't matter
who was first. I'll do it.

318
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:24,280
- It's mine.
- It's mine.

319
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:26,160
- Primprao.
- Nareewan.

320
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:28,440
- It's mine.
- It's mine.

321
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:30,120
- I'll do it--
- Keep it down!

322
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,120
This isn't a public market,

323
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,280
and it's well past dark.

324
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:38,240
My apologies, Jiam.

325
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,360
We'll go to bed right now.

326
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:44,720
Towel.

327
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:47,760
Thanks.

328
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:49,000
Hurry.

329
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,760
That's enough.

330
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:56,240
As for you,

331
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:59,040
instead of dallying around like this,

332
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:01,480
I suggest you start preparing

333
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:04,440
for what's coming after the will is read.

334
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,640
You mean the other relatives
will come after me

335
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,240
because I inherited the fortune?

336
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:10,400
Yes.

337
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:12,680
But it's worse than that.

338
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:14,360
Could you please elaborate?

339
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,720
She just says that and walks off?

340
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:21,680
This house is full of weirdos.

341
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:35,320
ALWAYS LOVE YOU, SASI
THATRI THATRIPAN

342
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:48,800
Almost done, Sasi? It's almost time.

343
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,760
Are you still hung up on him?

344
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,680
You're about to get engaged, Sasi.

345
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:00,280
I haven't forgotten, Mother.

346
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:04,440
I'm well aware
we're rushing to get engaged

347
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:06,960
without even breaking off
the old one with Thatri.

348
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,120
It's necessary.

349
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,160
Thatri has nothing left now.

350
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:12,160
But it's shameful, Mother.

351
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:16,800
It's too disgraceful for me to accept.

352
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:18,560
Then don't.

353
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:21,040
Just put all the blame on me.

354
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:23,360
I'd rather be the villain

355
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:26,320
than watch you live a life of poverty
with a man who has no future.

356
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:40,080
Let go of Thatri, Sasi.

357
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:43,480
He's no longer part of your future.

358
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,680
We're not poor,

359
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:50,200
but we're not wealthy either.

360
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:53,160
In these times of war,

361
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:56,640
how could women like us survive
without a man to protect us?

362
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,600
Trust me, Sasi.

363
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,120
Even if your fiancé isn't rich,

364
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,760
he has a bright future ahead.

365
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:08,640
And above all, he loves you deeply.

366
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:12,840
That just makes me feel
even more like a terrible person.

367
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,840
We've come too far.

368
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:17,600
There's no turning back now.

369
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:24,920
It's time.

370
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:34,400
Let's go, dear.

371
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:37,320
Keeping the elders waiting isn't proper.

372
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,240
Please.

373
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:45,440
Alright.

374
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:50,880
‪ALWAYS LOVE YOU, SASI
‪THATRI THATRIPAN

375
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:14,640
Who is that, Paetai?

376
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,560
That is District Chief Bandit.

377
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:20,280
He was just appointed to the post today.

378
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,840
Pae, why did you bring
the District Chief here?

379
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,440
Of course I had to invite him.

380
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,920
Just in case someone tries to hurt me

381
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,720
after I get the bigger portion,

382
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:40,160
he'll be here as my witness.

383
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:44,200
- Right this way, then.
- Yes, madam.

384
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,800
Everyone is present.
Stop stalling, Vijarn.

385
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:58,600
Let's see between the ones who worked
or the ones who did nothing,

386
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,800
who'll get the bigger cut?

387
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:07,200
Very well. I shall begin reading the will.

388
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,080
Yes.

389
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:21,280
"I, Mr. Som Adisuan, confirm that

390
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,600
I am of sound mind and body

391
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:26,600
while drafting this will.

392
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:30,400
I wish to distribute my assets

393
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:34,040
as follows.

394
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:36,240
The 300,000 baht central fund

395
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:39,920
in the iron chest at home
shall be granted to…

396
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:46,400
Mr. Thatri Vorapat,

397
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:51,600
son of my sister,

398
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,600
and Ms. Rajit Adisuan,

399
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:56,000
formerly known as Suksakaw.

400
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:59,440
She's my niece.
It'll be divided equally between them."

401
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:06,440
Congratulations, Mr. Thatri.

402
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:08,880
Thank, Nid.

403
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:13,280
"As for the jewelry in the iron chest,

404
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:14,920
consisting

405
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,720
of the diamond-encrusted emerald set,

406
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:19,960
the necklace, rings, earrings,

407
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:21,440
bracelets,

408
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:24,160
and the marquise-cut
five-carat diamond ring,

409
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,560
I bequeath these

410
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,960
to Ms. Rajit Adisuan.

411
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:30,640
For the six gold watches

412
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:32,960
and the three-carat
rectangular diamond ring,

413
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:36,160
I bequeath these in their entirety
to Mr. Thatri Vorapat.

414
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:44,720
As for all 26 plots of land,

415
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:46,160
totaling 2,000 rai,

416
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,520
the three tin mines,

417
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:51,040
eight shophouse complexes,

418
00:29:51,120 --> 00:29:52,720
Som Song Saeng House,

419
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,480
ten million baht in cash,

420
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:58,120
and all shares in my various businesses,

421
00:29:58,720 --> 00:30:00,800
as specified in the asset list

422
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,480
attached to this will,

423
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,720
are to be distributed to…

424
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:09,240
Mr. Thatri Vorapat and Ms. Rajit Adisuan,

425
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:11,120
fifty-fifty, equally."

426
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,280
- What?
- That concludes the will.

427
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,200
Huh?

428
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:14,320
What is this?

429
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:18,040
- Hey!
- Is this real?

430
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:24,560
Wai!

431
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:26,360
Wai, stop!

432
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:28,880
I told you,
we're nothing but servants here.

433
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,680
Why are you dreaming of that inheritance?

434
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:31,920
You're delusional.

435
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,000
We are not servants!
You know that, Mother!

436
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:40,840
Can we just stop bringing this up?

437
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:43,560
We've already gotten
quite a lot over the years.

438
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:46,120
It's nothing compared
to what those two got!

439
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,920
Wai!

440
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,480
Stop it! Do you want to end up unemployed?

441
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:56,360
Don't dwell on it, Wai.

442
00:30:57,600 --> 00:31:00,360
Just accept that that fortune
was never meant for us.

443
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:03,640
Let's just sit back
and watch them fight over it.

444
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:06,680
It's much more entertaining that way.

445
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:14,000
Fraud!

446
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,280
This will is rigged!

447
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:16,360
Agreed.

448
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:19,040
Why did everything
go to just the two of them?

449
00:31:19,120 --> 00:31:20,000
Right.

450
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:21,160
Right?

451
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:23,320
Why did we get nothing?

452
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:25,920
My apologies, Miss Paetai.

453
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:31,560
There's a duplicate copy of Mr. Som's will
at the District Office.

454
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,280
If you have any doubts,
you're welcome to go there and verify

455
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,760
that the contents are identical.

456
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,360
It's alright, Pae.

457
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,640
Even if Uncle didn't leave us anything,
we have our own means.

458
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:43,120
Don't be angry.

459
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:45,120
How am I supposed to stay calm?

460
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,080
How can you expect me not to be furious?

461
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:49,680
I can accept Rajit.

462
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:52,080
She's a niece and shares the family name.

463
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:54,040
But him?

464
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:55,800
He's the son of an affair.

465
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:58,880
He's not even a blood relative.

466
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:00,040
How did he end up with this?

467
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:02,360
- You, why did--
- That's enough, Aunt Paetai.

468
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,920
You have no right
to speak about his mother like that.

469
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,920
Hey, you naive little girl.

470
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:10,840
What do you know about anything, huh?

471
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:13,200
You've got your share, now get lost!
Don't meddle in this.

472
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:14,440
Excuse me,

473
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:15,960
but I'm not going anywhere.

474
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:17,840
Because what you're saying

475
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:19,880
is completely unfair to Uncle Ree.

476
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:22,400
If you have a problem with him,

477
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:25,040
leave his parents out of this.

478
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:28,240
- You!
- My apologies, Miss Paetai.

479
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:30,880
I think…

480
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:32,520
If you have a dispute,

481
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,480
I suggest we leave it to the law.

482
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:38,040
There's no need for physical force.

483
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:41,520
As District Chief,
I cannot allow that to happen.

484
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:45,840
If we can't use force,

485
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:48,040
we'll use the law!

486
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:51,720
There's no way we're letting outsiders
steal what's rightfully ours.

487
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:53,000
Agreed.

488
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:56,640
You'd better watch your back.

489
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:04,400
Pardon us.

490
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:15,080
I'm so sorry, Thatri.

491
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:18,240
Pae, wait.

492
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:24,920
Thank you very much, District Chief.

493
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,000
It's my duty.

494
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:30,280
If you'll excuse me.

495
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:46,960
Thanks for earlier.

496
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,560
It's nothing.

497
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:54,040
I just did what was right.

498
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,440
Everything's settled.

499
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:04,560
I'll be heading back to Bangkok today.

500
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,600
Not just yet, Mr. Thatri.

501
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,199
You must stay to settle

502
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,679
all the necessary paperwork
related to the will first.

503
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,120
And how long will that take?

504
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:14,960
Approximately three to six months, sir.

505
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Six months?

506
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:33,440
BANGKOK NOI HOSPITAL

507
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:35,199
<i>You Wild Bull,</i>

508
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,880
<i>what did you get me into?</i>

509
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:40,320
<i>You swore this would be a few-day trip,</i>
<i>and then I'd be off to Chiang Mai.</i>

510
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:43,120
<i>But now I'm stuck here</i>
<i>for three to six months.</i>

511
00:34:43,199 --> 00:34:45,600
<i>What the hell am I supposed</i>
<i>to do now, you jerk?</i>

512
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:51,480
Thatri,

513
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:54,840
why did you send your friend
into such trouble?

514
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:56,960
You know full well

515
00:34:57,040 --> 00:34:59,920
how vicious those relatives are.

516
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:02,200
Even your own mother
had to flee from that house.

517
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,280
Mom, please.

518
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:06,800
If I hadn't told him that,
would he have agreed to go?

519
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:10,600
That much inheritance,

520
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:12,600
it would be a waste to just let it go.

521
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,920
Don't you want it?

522
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:18,840
Uncle Som left you struggling for so long.

523
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:21,480
And what if they tear your friend apart?

524
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:23,360
What will you do then?

525
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:24,640
Don't worry, Mom.

526
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:27,920
Leopard is tough and smart.

527
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,080
I'm confident

528
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:35,720
those people can't touch him.

529
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:38,400
If you send him a telegram,

530
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:40,280
please tell him to just hang in there.

531
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:42,080
Damn you…

532
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:45,480
You are such a troublemaker.

533
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,360
I know you're worried about him.

534
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:52,200
I'm worried about him too.

535
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:00,680
<i>Don't overthink it, buddy.</i>
<i>Just let what everyone says</i>

536
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:02,720
<i>go in one ear and out the other.</i>

537
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,800
<i>As soon as I'm healed, I'll be there.</i>

538
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:07,360
<i>For now, just hang in there.</i>

539
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:08,640
<i>Love and best wishes,</i>

540
00:36:08,720 --> 00:36:10,800
<i>your friend, the Wild Bull.</i>

541
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:13,200
You lunatic! "Hang in there"?

542
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,600
Don't let me catch you.

543
00:36:14,680 --> 00:36:16,680
You're gonna pay for this, you Wild Bull.

544
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,440
What are you ranting about
all by yourself?

545
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:30,280
What is it?

546
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:33,680
Oh, well,

547
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:35,880
Mr. Vijarn asked me to come and get you.

548
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:41,040
While the process is pending,

549
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:44,640
both of you will receive an advance
from the central fund.

550
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:45,640
Here you are.

551
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:48,040
Thanks.

552
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:04,120
Here. This is the two baht I owed you.

553
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:14,280
You seem quite happy, Mr. Thatri.

554
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:16,000
Do you have an urgent expense?

555
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:34,880
Why are you still following me?
I've already paid you back.

556
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:38,280
I'm here for the "dog", obviously.

557
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:41,000
No need to stress that point so hard.

558
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:51,400
How's Don Jose doing, Doc?

559
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,720
He can head home now,

560
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:54,720
but he still needs close monitoring.

561
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:57,440
I've written the care instructions
on the medicine label.

562
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:58,960
Make sure you follow them.

563
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:03,240
Don't worry, I'll take
the best care of him.

564
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:08,200
Oh, you're so cute. Are you hungry?

565
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:10,000
I'll get you something to eat.

566
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,120
You're such a good boy!

567
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:21,080
Here you go.

568
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:28,000
Easy there, Don Jose.

569
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:30,520
Don Jose?

570
00:38:30,600 --> 00:38:33,880
- Is that the dog's name?
- Yes.

571
00:38:33,960 --> 00:38:36,440
What's the meaning behind it?

572
00:38:36,520 --> 00:38:39,040
It's from the opera "Don Giovanni",

573
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:40,760
by Mozart.

574
00:38:41,600 --> 00:38:43,280
But I prefer calling him Don Jose.

575
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:46,200
The melody is so exquisite,
you'll never forget it.

576
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,120
You've seen an opera, Uncle Ree?

577
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:52,280
And you know Mozart?

578
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,360
Mr. Vijarn told me

579
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:57,200
you only finished secondary school.

580
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:01,680
Well, back when I used

581
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:03,720
to mow lawns at this wealthy estate…

582
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:07,320
I'd hear them playing it.

583
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,120
I just loved it, so I remembered it.

584
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:12,800
Hold on. Does a rich family

585
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,920
really own Mozart records?

586
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:16,280
Of course they do.

587
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:19,080
How else would I have gotten
the name Don Jose?

588
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:28,320
Eat up, Don Jose, my baby.

589
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:51,080
Who's that?

590
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:49,480
Who are you?

591
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:51,520
Why are you sneaking around
Som Song Saeng House?

592
00:41:09,120 --> 00:41:10,400
District Chief?

593
00:41:12,080 --> 00:41:13,680
Have you decided to become a criminal?

594
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,720
Are you insane?

595
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:17,760
I'm no criminal in a government uniform.

596
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:20,720
Oh really?

597
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:22,560
Then why break into this place

598
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:23,840
wearing a ski mask, too?

599
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:29,760
I'm on an official mission

600
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,280
to take down Zhang Gong Cheng.

601
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:34,960
Zhang Gong Cheng?

602
00:41:35,040 --> 00:41:36,240
Yes,

603
00:41:37,040 --> 00:41:38,120
Zhang Gong Cheng,

604
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:41,480
also known as Blackbeard.

605
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:44,880
<i>He's a pirate who terrorizes</i>
<i>the ships in these waters,</i>

606
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:47,240
<i>leaving nothing but ruin in his wake.</i>

607
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:50,480
<i>He frequently raids</i>
<i>the local fishing villages, too.</i>

608
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:52,720
Eliminate them all!

609
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:02,440
Take every single valuable

610
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:04,120
and all their supplies!

611
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:06,200
Yes, Boss! Grab the bags!

612
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:07,480
Clear everything out!

613
00:42:07,560 --> 00:42:09,160
Give it!

614
00:42:09,240 --> 00:42:10,560
Give me!

615
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:12,480
Give me everything.

616
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:14,640
Take everything!

617
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:20,040
Hurry! Take this.

618
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:23,640
Here, take this.

619
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:26,880
Please, have mercy.
Please spare our lives.

620
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,440
Take whatever you want.

621
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:49,040
<i>He raids everyone.</i>

622
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,440
<i>He shows no mercy.</i>

623
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:55,240
<i>No one dares to stand against him.</i>

624
00:42:57,160 --> 00:42:59,400
Lord Phithak, my superior,

625
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:02,360
has ordered me to investigate this matter

626
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:03,840
and bring him to justice.

627
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:08,560
Zhang Gong Cheng, known as Blackbeard,

628
00:43:08,640 --> 00:43:12,200
he must have someone protecting him,
or we would've stopped him by now.

629
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:14,240
I need you to go to Phuket

630
00:43:14,320 --> 00:43:16,440
and deal with this matter immediately.

631
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:23,000
Understood, sir.

632
00:43:24,320 --> 00:43:26,120
What does that have to do with this house?

633
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:29,080
Because a lot of the stolen goods

634
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:32,120
were sold through
the Som Song Saeng company.

635
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:34,000
That doesn't prove anything.

636
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:36,200
Goods change hands all the time.

637
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:38,640
That doesn't mean
they're linked to pirates.

638
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:40,480
True.

639
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:42,640
But this is the only lead I have,

640
00:43:43,560 --> 00:43:46,440
so this is where
I'm starting my investigation.

641
00:43:47,360 --> 00:43:48,880
Possibility or not,

642
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:51,520
breaking into my family's home

643
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:53,200
makes you no better than a thief.

644
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:55,360
I should report you.

645
00:43:56,080 --> 00:43:59,000
Are you sure that Som Song Saeng House

646
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:01,720
is really your family?

647
00:44:04,480 --> 00:44:05,640
Of course it is.

648
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:08,680
If it's not my family, then who is it?

649
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:11,240
Is that so…

650
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:16,480
Mr. Thatri Thatripan?

651
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:28,320
You know who I am?

652
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:33,440
You may not know me,
but a prominent socialite like you?

653
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:35,120
I know you all too well.

654
00:44:47,720 --> 00:44:52,200
THE BILLIONAIRE DONATES 1,000 BAHT
TO FLOOD VICTIMS IN THE NORTH

655
00:44:56,440 --> 00:44:57,640
Sir.

656
00:45:00,240 --> 00:45:01,440
This is Mr. Wisarut.

657
00:45:01,520 --> 00:45:04,920
He's a businessman.
I've worked with him in the past.

658
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,400
If I could land someone like Thatri,

659
00:45:07,480 --> 00:45:10,240
I'd be in heaven
for the rest of my life, wouldn't I?

660
00:45:10,320 --> 00:45:13,360
That's right.

661
00:45:13,440 --> 00:45:14,840
So handsome.

662
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:17,880
He has such impeccable manners
and a sharp business mind.

663
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:21,760
So, what's it going to be, Mr. Thatri?

664
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:25,640
Are you still going to have me arrested
for trespassing Som Song Saeng House?

665
00:45:25,720 --> 00:45:27,920
Because I could
tell everyone in this house

666
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:30,200
- exactly who you really are.
- Keep it down.

667
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:33,360
I'm only doing this

668
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:35,520
because my friend Thatri begged me to.

669
00:45:35,600 --> 00:45:37,240
Thatri, your friend?

670
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:40,960
Yes. Thatri of this house
and I are friends.

671
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:43,000
But he was severely wounded
in an explosion,

672
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:45,600
and he couldn't make it
to claim the inheritance.

673
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:56,320
Wild Bull.

674
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:00,920
If he didn't show up,
he'd lose the inheritance.

675
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:05,200
Yes. So he asked me to take his place.

676
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:10,520
District Chief, can you please
keep this a secret for now?

677
00:46:10,600 --> 00:46:11,960
Fine.

678
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:13,720
But there has to be a trade.

679
00:46:16,640 --> 00:46:17,840
A trade?

680
00:46:17,920 --> 00:46:19,680
I want you to help me find out

681
00:46:19,760 --> 00:46:21,560
who in Som Song Saeng House

682
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:24,080
is backing Zhang Gong Cheng.

683
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:31,320
Fine.

684
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:34,520
It's not like I have other choice.

685
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,440
Mr. Thatri.

686
00:46:47,320 --> 00:46:48,600
Heading out already?

687
00:46:48,680 --> 00:46:50,040
I'm going to the mines.

688
00:46:50,120 --> 00:46:52,000
I'm going to check
on Uncle Som's business.

689
00:46:52,760 --> 00:46:54,200
Like you'd understand anything.

690
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:56,840
You've never worked,

691
00:46:56,920 --> 00:46:58,120
yet you're the one inheriting everything.

692
00:46:58,760 --> 00:46:59,960
I wonder what Mr. Som was thinking.

693
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:09,400
Don't mind Wai, he's always like that.

694
00:47:09,480 --> 00:47:11,280
Please don't take it to heart.

695
00:47:11,360 --> 00:47:12,960
I'm off to class now.

696
00:47:13,520 --> 00:47:17,040
Focus on your studies. Don't forget
to come back and feed Don Jose.

697
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:18,640
Sure thing.

698
00:47:32,080 --> 00:47:34,080
Dressed up like that.
What's the occasion?

699
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:36,080
To the mines.

700
00:47:37,240 --> 00:47:38,360
To the mines?

701
00:47:39,200 --> 00:47:41,000
Can you handle that?

702
00:47:41,080 --> 00:47:42,640
You're a lady,

703
00:47:42,720 --> 00:47:45,160
better off staying home
and waiting for your allowance.

704
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:48,240
How dare you! It's just the mines.

705
00:47:48,320 --> 00:47:50,040
Why wouldn't I be able to handle it?

706
00:47:50,680 --> 00:47:53,320
Grandfather entrusted them to me.

707
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:55,000
I can definitely handle it.

708
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:57,120
Well, let's see

709
00:47:57,200 --> 00:47:59,520
how long you last out there, Rajit.

710
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:02,800
Challenge accepted. Just you wait and see.

711
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:04,280
Fine by me.

712
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:06,280
I'm dying to see it.

713
00:48:08,720 --> 00:48:11,280
Wai, let's go.

714
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:12,560
Understood.

715
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:23,760
ADISUAN MINES

716
00:48:30,320 --> 00:48:31,840
This is called an opencast mining.

717
00:48:33,120 --> 00:48:36,520
After excavation,
it creates this pit-like shape.

718
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:39,000
Workers then dig

719
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:43,120
and transport the rocks, gravel,
and clay to the sluice channels.

720
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:46,360
- So, the ore is mixed in with that soil?
- Yes, sir.

721
00:48:46,440 --> 00:48:48,320
The crude ore extracted
from this soil and rock

722
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:49,520
will undergo further processing.

723
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:58,480
Oh! Mr. Vijarn!

724
00:49:00,800 --> 00:49:01,840
Mr. Thatri,

725
00:49:01,920 --> 00:49:04,520
meet Sak, our mine lessee.

726
00:49:05,120 --> 00:49:07,320
This is Mr. Thatri, Mr. Som's nephew.

727
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:11,920
How's the work going here?

728
00:49:14,000 --> 00:49:16,760
Just thinking about it is exhausting.

729
00:49:16,840 --> 00:49:19,720
The war has crashed the tin prices

730
00:49:20,640 --> 00:49:22,400
down to 30 baht per hap.

731
00:49:23,200 --> 00:49:25,600
I don't know how I'm supposed
to make any profit.

732
00:49:26,720 --> 00:49:27,920
Sak.

733
00:49:28,920 --> 00:49:32,480
But the rent must still be paid on time.

734
00:49:33,840 --> 00:49:36,480
Before Mr. Som passed away,
he entrusted this matter to me.

735
00:49:38,960 --> 00:49:40,520
No problem at all.

736
00:49:41,240 --> 00:49:44,960
I certainly wouldn't want
Mr. Som's ghost

737
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:47,160
coming back to haunt me for the rent.

738
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:49,880
That sounds incredibly tough.

739
00:50:04,680 --> 00:50:05,640
Excuse me, Auntie.

740
00:50:06,280 --> 00:50:08,280
What is that tool you're holding called?

741
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:10,640
Oh, this? It's called a Liang, dear.

742
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:12,520
- A Liang?
- Yes, dear.

743
00:50:21,440 --> 00:50:23,120
I thought you came here to work?

744
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:25,280
You've been standing there for ages.

745
00:50:28,720 --> 00:50:30,000
This is part of the work.

746
00:50:30,080 --> 00:50:32,160
Why do you always
have to pick a fight with me?

747
00:50:33,520 --> 00:50:35,440
Watching them pan for ore?

748
00:50:35,520 --> 00:50:36,320
Is that what you call working?

749
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:39,440
I'm just curious
to see how it's done.

750
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:41,520
As if you'd try it yourself.

751
00:50:41,600 --> 00:50:42,840
Judging by your look,

752
00:50:43,480 --> 00:50:45,680
- I don't think you have it in you.
- Who says I can't?

753
00:50:45,760 --> 00:50:48,720
I can do it. But what about you?

754
00:50:49,320 --> 00:50:51,160
All you do is talk.

755
00:50:51,240 --> 00:50:52,240
Can you actually do it?

756
00:50:52,840 --> 00:50:53,840
All I do is talk, huh?

757
00:50:55,160 --> 00:50:56,240
Then let's race.

758
00:50:56,840 --> 00:50:58,520
Let's see who can pan the most ore.

759
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:00,840
Fine.

760
00:51:03,160 --> 00:51:04,360
- Go, Miss Rajit.
- Go, Miss Rajit.

761
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:06,160
- You can do it.
- You can do it.

762
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:07,520
- Go, Miss Rajit.
- Go, Miss Rajit.

763
00:51:10,560 --> 00:51:12,800
- Go, Miss Rajit.
- Go, Miss Rajit.

764
00:51:12,880 --> 00:51:15,280
Go, Miss Rajit.

765
00:51:15,360 --> 00:51:17,240
Go, Miss Rajit.

766
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:22,360
You're shaking that pan so hard,

767
00:51:22,440 --> 00:51:24,200
the ore is falling back into the water.

768
00:51:25,920 --> 00:51:28,240
Save your breath. Look at your own pan.

769
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:30,200
There's nothing left but water.

770
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:40,280
I'm giving you a head start.

771
00:51:40,360 --> 00:51:43,440
Giving me a head start?
Or do you just not know how to do it?

772
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:44,960
Stop making excuses.

773
00:51:45,920 --> 00:51:48,400
At the end of the day,
it's all about the ore in the pan.

774
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:49,680
Whoever has the most wins.

775
00:51:50,720 --> 00:51:52,320
I'm definitely going to win.

776
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:56,080
Don't get so cocky, little girl.

777
00:51:56,160 --> 00:51:57,560
Just wait and see.

778
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,920
Is that all you got, Uncle Ree?

779
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:10,400
Oh, you're losing all the ore.

780
00:52:10,480 --> 00:52:11,920
Just keep panning.

781
00:52:13,960 --> 00:52:16,320
Whoa, yours is just water.

782
00:52:16,400 --> 00:52:17,400
This thing is garbage.

783
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:19,800
Just keep panning.

784
00:52:35,520 --> 00:52:36,640
Tin ore, anyone?

785
00:52:36,720 --> 00:52:38,480
Sir, would you like to buy some tin?

786
00:52:41,640 --> 00:52:42,680
Tin ore, anyone?

787
00:52:43,680 --> 00:52:46,520
We'll take it all. How much?

788
00:52:47,520 --> 00:52:49,200
For everything, it's--

789
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:51,040
And how much for you? What's your price?

790
00:52:53,480 --> 00:52:55,720
Acting like you actually
recovered a fortune.

791
00:52:56,800 --> 00:52:59,560
Look who's talking. You're no different.

792
00:53:13,760 --> 00:53:15,360
No! Stop!

793
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:17,640
Stop it!

794
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:20,560
Help, someone!

795
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:22,560
Help us!

796
00:53:22,640 --> 00:53:25,200
Stop right there!
Don't you dare touch them!

797
00:53:25,280 --> 00:53:26,880
Hey. Miss Rajit.

798
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:29,440
You can't go near them.
They're armed with swords.

799
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:32,880
Help us!

800
00:53:34,200 --> 00:53:35,560
If we just watch,
the villagers are going to get hurt.

801
00:53:38,320 --> 00:53:39,960
- Hey.
- Uncle Ree!

802
00:54:04,840 --> 00:54:05,960
Mr. Thatri…

803
00:54:17,240 --> 00:54:18,120
Uncle Ree.

804
00:54:20,560 --> 00:54:23,840
If you wish to test your blade,
come to me.

805
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:36,120
ADISUAN MINES

806
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:38,800
Soldiers,

807
00:54:40,240 --> 00:54:42,080
why are you harassing these villagers?

808
00:54:42,720 --> 00:54:44,600
Thai people are our allies!

809
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:47,160
To harm a friend

810
00:54:48,240 --> 00:54:50,080
is to disgrace the honor

811
00:54:51,760 --> 00:54:53,560
of the Children of the Sun!

812
00:55:43,880 --> 00:55:45,880
Ouch! Take it easy.

813
00:55:46,480 --> 00:55:47,800
Is that a gentle touch or what?

814
00:55:47,880 --> 00:55:50,120
Just bear with it.
It's not near your heart.

815
00:55:50,760 --> 00:55:51,960
You didn't seem

816
00:55:52,040 --> 00:55:55,320
so afraid of pain when you were fighting
those Japanese soldiers earlier.

817
00:55:56,120 --> 00:55:57,400
I got carried away back then.

818
00:55:59,320 --> 00:56:00,520
All done.

819
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:08,400
Mr. Thatri, how is the wound?

820
00:56:09,520 --> 00:56:11,800
I'm alright. No need for a doctor.

821
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:15,560
You were screaming like a pig.

822
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:21,160
Well, I'll be off then.

823
00:56:21,240 --> 00:56:22,880
I'm meeting Aunt Paetai.

824
00:56:23,760 --> 00:56:24,800
Coming with me?

825
00:56:25,960 --> 00:56:27,600
I came alone. I can leave alone.

826
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:32,720
ADISUAN MINES

827
00:56:40,600 --> 00:56:41,560
Mr. Vijarn,

828
00:56:42,720 --> 00:56:44,200
who is this Japanese officer?

829
00:56:44,280 --> 00:56:46,840
Ah, this is Colonel Nakamura.

830
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:48,480
He's stationed here.

831
00:56:49,200 --> 00:56:51,200
He regularly buys tin from us

832
00:56:51,800 --> 00:56:54,760
and is a loyal customer
of Mr. Som's company as well.

833
00:56:56,840 --> 00:56:57,760
Colonel Nakamura,

834
00:56:58,800 --> 00:56:59,960
meet Mr. Thatri.

835
00:57:03,680 --> 00:57:06,040
It seems you hold Thai people
in high regard, Colonel.

836
00:57:09,880 --> 00:57:13,160
The war makes life difficult for the Thai.

837
00:57:13,760 --> 00:57:15,960
With bandits robbing the locals,

838
00:57:16,720 --> 00:57:19,320
I simply do not want my soldiers

839
00:57:20,080 --> 00:57:22,280
to be an additional burden.

840
00:57:25,280 --> 00:57:26,840
Such a true leader.

841
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:35,280
Speaking of bandits, Colonel,
are you familiar with Zhang Gong Cheng?

842
00:57:36,360 --> 00:57:38,080
That Blackbeard pirate,

843
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:40,240
who hasn't heard of him?

844
00:57:41,080 --> 00:57:43,400
I want him captured immediately.

845
00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:46,440
He raids Japanese supply ships

846
00:57:47,240 --> 00:57:49,680
just as often as he attacks the Thai.

847
00:58:00,040 --> 00:58:00,960
Honestly,

848
00:58:01,040 --> 00:58:03,200
I don't trust anyone in this family.

849
00:58:03,280 --> 00:58:05,440
It's obvious they're all
just after the inheritance.

850
00:58:05,520 --> 00:58:07,160
Why should I give up the inheritance?

851
00:58:07,240 --> 00:58:09,520
Because they believe you're the grandson,

852
00:58:09,600 --> 00:58:10,800
but you're not.

853
00:58:10,880 --> 00:58:12,480
<i>I feel so guilty.</i>

854
00:58:12,560 --> 00:58:14,320
I shouldn't have sent you there.

855
00:58:14,400 --> 00:58:15,720
‪NEXT EPISODE

856
00:58:16,440 --> 00:58:17,520
<i>Something's happened to Miss Rajit.</i>

857
00:58:17,600 --> 00:58:18,760
It would be for the best

858
00:58:18,840 --> 00:58:19,880
if something did happen to her.

859
00:58:19,960 --> 00:58:22,840
You are the one closest to the suspect.

860
00:58:22,920 --> 00:58:25,520
If you won't help me,
how am I supposed to continue?

861
00:58:25,600 --> 00:58:26,520
You know how dangerous it is

862
00:58:26,600 --> 00:58:28,760
to bring American soldiers into the house?

863
00:58:28,840 --> 00:58:30,000
If the Japanese find out,

864
00:58:30,080 --> 00:58:31,320
we'll all be in deep trouble.

865
00:59:03,840 --> 00:59:05,640
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
